Package: fireData
Title: Connecting R to Google Firebase
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Robin", "Kohze", email = "Robin@Kohze.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Paul", "Spende", role = "aut"),
    person("Kevin", "McGinley", role = "ctb")
  )
Description: Provides comprehensive API access to Google Firebase services including
    Realtime Database, Cloud Firestore, Authentication, Cloud Storage, Dynamic Links,
    and Remote Config. Supports both interactive (Shiny apps, R console) and automated
    (CI/CD, server-side) workflows. Use cases include creating user logins with
    persistent data storage for mobile apps, Shiny applications, or IoT applications.
    See the fireData GitHub repository for more information.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
